    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing connection status notification in user API close\n\n### Summary\nWhen `user_api_close()` is called, it directly closes the connection endpoint without sending any notification to the user application about the connection being terminated. This causes the user application to miss a mandatory information element in outgoing signaling messages, leading to potential synchronization issues.\n\nThis fix adds a connection status notification mechanism that informs the user application when the connection is being closed.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/API/USER/user_indication.h`: Added `USER_IND_CONN` notification type and `user_ind_conn_t` structure\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/API/USER/user_api.c`: \n  - Added `_user_api_connection_handler` function to handle connection status notifications\n  - Registered the new handler in `user_api_initialize`\n  - Modified `user_api_close` to send connection closed notification before closing endpoint\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Establish a connection through the user API\n2. Call `user_api_close()` \n3. Observe that no connection status notification is sent to the user application\n4. User application may experience synchronization issues due to missing connection status information\n\nThe fix ensures that when `user_api_close()` is called, a proper connection status notification is sent before the connection endpoint is closed, resolving the missing mandatory information element issue.\n"
}